		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Codex Gigas</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:182px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Devil_codex_Gigas.jpg" class="image" title="The codex is the largest medieval manuscript in the world."><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e4/Devil_codex_Gigas.jpg/180px-Devil_codex_Gigas.jpg" width="180" height="124" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Devil_codex_Gigas.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
The codex is the largest medieval manuscript in the world.</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>The <i><b>Codex Gigas</b></i> (<a href="/wiki/English_language" title="English language">English</a>: <span lang="en" xml:lang="en"><i>Giant Book</i></span>) is the largest extant medieval <a href="/wiki/Manuscript" title="Manuscript">manuscript</a> in the world<sup id="cite_ref-kb.se_0-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-kb.se-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup>. It was created in the early 13th century in the <a href="/wiki/Benedictine" title="Benedictine">Benedictine</a> <a href="/wiki/Monastery_of_Podla%C5%BEice" title="Monastery of Podlažice" class="mw-redirect">monastery of Podlažice</a> in <a href="/wiki/Bohemia" title="Bohemia">Bohemia</a>, and is now preserved at the <a href="/wiki/National_Library_of_Sweden" title="National Library of Sweden">National Library of Sweden</a> in <a href="/wiki/Stockholm" title="Stockholm">Stockholm</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-kb.se_0-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-kb.se-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> It is also known as the <i><b>Devil's Bible</b></i> due to a large illustration of the devil on the inside and the legend surrounding its creation.</p>
